latestPosts.caption:
I’ve always loved pieces that carry weight — not just in style, but in story. ✨

The 1989–97 Chicago Bulls away jersey? It’s one of them. And @jerseystation.ind gave me the best piece, custom printer with my name and favorite number. ❤️

It reminds me that culture never stays in one place. What starts on the court can end up everywhere — on stage, on the street, in closets like mine. 😅

This carousel is my little tribute to a piece of sports history that became fashion history.

Hope you enjoy it as much as I loved creating it!

Special thanks to @altabelleza_bysm for the amazing photos! 📸
@kripathankachan_makeupartist for making me look fly! 💋
📍location courtesy: @sthalamstudios

latestPosts.caption:
It’s been a while since l’ve shared something here, and I’ve been thinking about where to begin. So, I thought l’d start with something that truly inspired me recently-  @kappacultr ❤️

Last month, I had the incredible opportunity to attend this one-of-a-kind music festival right here in Kochi, Kerala. For three unforgettable days, I immersed myself in the music, the energy, and the sheer creativity that this festival brought to life. And honestly, it inspired me to get back to creating content
-my way. 

This carousel is my humble attempt to relive and share the magic of Kappa Cultr. I’m no professional editor/ designer, but I wanted to create something that could evoke the same emotions I felt during those days-joy, freedom, and pure awe.

A huge shoutout to the incredible creative team behind Kappa Cultr. Some of you are dear friends and colleagues I’ve had the privilege of working with in the past, and seeing your hard work come to life was nothing short of inspiring. From the workshops to the stage design and the overall vibes, you’ve set a new standard for events in India. Congratulations on pulling off something so extraordinary! 💫

Special shoutout to @nowinbody, you are a true visionary! 🥹
@janani_kalasutra @slackyogi @lostkidsgarage 
@stardust_flows - y’all were shining so bright that this event wouldn’t have been the same without your light! 🌈⚡️ Here’s to more music, more creativity, and more moments that take our breath away. 🖤 

To everyone who attended Kappa Cultr this year—what was your favorite moment? Let’s relive the magic together and celebrate this milestone for Kochi! 🎉 

#KappaCultr #KochiDiaries #MusicFestival #Artculture #kochivibes #musiclover #calmchor #technomusic

latestPosts.caption:
There are moments in life when you question your path and wonder if you’ll ever find your way back. Last year, as my focus shifted to other projects and aspects of my life, I found myself wondering if I could still reconnect with the creative work that has always brought me joy and purpose.

And then, this happened. I am deeply honored to receive the Madhavikutty-Kamala Surraya Short Story Award for Best Actress in a Music Video for my work in Penmai. 🎖️

This award holds special significance as it is named after Madhavikutty, also known as Kamala Surayya—a fearless, trailblazing author whose work challenged societal norms and explored themes of identity, love, and freedom. She was a woman ahead of her time, unafraid to speak her truth despite the criticism and hardships she faced. Kamala Surayya was often unappreciated during her lifetime. Her candid explorations of personal experiences and emotions challenged societal norms, and she became an icon for women striving for liberation from oppression. 

Receiving this award for Penmai feels even more meaningful, as the music video tells the story of a woman who is a prostitute—abused and oppressed by many—who ultimately takes revenge on those who wronged her. It’s a powerful narrative that highlights the struggles of those who are oppressed by their circumstances and serves as a reminder of the strength and resilience that lies within us all. ✨

At a time when I felt uncertain about returning to my passions, this award has become a profound reminder to believe in myself and unlock my true potential. It feels like the universe encouraging me to embrace my journey, despite the challenges. 

I am incredibly grateful to the amazing team behind Penmai for trusting me with this character and bringing this story to life with such dedication. This award belongs as much to them as it does to me. 💞

@hrithwiksasikumar @hrishi.8o8 @insane_aki_ @vedanwithword @glen.correya @alt.plus_ @karuppdesigns - this wouldn’t have been possible without you guys. ❤️

latestPosts.caption:
September when by in a blink so here is a little #SeptemberDump ⭐️
I’ve been a little off socials last month purely because of how hectic it was. Onam took over with all its hype and it was @monkeydog_unleashed ’s first Onam in the state. It’s truly amazing to see someone outside of our little state appreciate the culture better than us. I learned a lot in the process of showing him around and sharing all the stories around this beautiful festival. Despite being away from home and missing the family, this Onam was really beautiful! 🌼 Kudos to @nbtbiz on their growth and a fun celebration! 
Our days were super packed with workload and shoots so we took some time out to explore kochi a little bit. We took a ride on the Water metro for the first time and I showed Danny the true glory of a proper Kulukki Sarbath! 🍹
On busy days, we had food outside checking out new spots and on sick days we cooked some food and stayed in bed to a comedy. Some days we would take random rides to @forum_kochi and play around with whatever cameras we had cuz it’s the only place usually open near us late into the night after we are done with work! Last month taught me a lot about keeping our inner children happy no matter how crazy life can get. There were so many times we truly felt exhausted and everything felt impossible to handle. I am truly grateful for the tiny moments in between that kept me alive and grateful to the friends and family who stuck with me. ✨
So as we welcome a new month and the final quarter of this year, I hope all of us remember to check in with ourselves. I wish we all embrace the joy of little things, the art of saying no and prioritizing what truly matters to us. ❤️

P.S @monkeydog_unleashed will probably tell you that he did all cooking. 🤪

#photodump #septemberdump #modellife #kochidiaries #onam2024
